dhcpServMib.name: dhcpServMib
dhcpServMib.contactinfo: James Offutt Postal: Lucent Technologies 400 Lapp Road Malvern, PA 19355 USA Tel: +1 610-722-7900 Fax: +1 610-725-8559
dhcpServMib.description: The Vendor Specific MIB module for entities implementing the server side of the Bootstrap Protocol (BOOTP) and the Dynamic Host Configuration protocol (DHCP) for Internet Protocol version 4 (IPv4).

dhcpServMibObjects.name: dhcpServMibObjects
dhcpServMibObjects.description: DHCP Server MIB objects are all defined in this branch.

dhcpServSystem.name: dhcpServSystem
dhcpServSystem.description: Group of objects that are related to the overall system.

dhcpServSubnetCounters.name: dhcpServSubnetCounters
dhcpServSubnetCounters.description: Group of objects that count various subnet data values

dhcpServBootpCounters.name: dhcpServBootpCounters
dhcpServBootpCounters.description: Group of objects that count various BOOTP events.

dhcpServDhcpCounters.name: dhcpServDhcpCounters
dhcpServDhcpCounters.description: Group of objects that count various DHCP Statistics.

dhcpServBootpStatistics.name: dhcpServBootpStatistics
dhcpServBootpStatistics.description: Group of objects that measure various BOOTP statistics.

dhcpServDhcpStatistics.name: dhcpServDhcpStatistics
dhcpServDhcpStatistics.description: Group of objects that measure various DHCP statistics.

dhcpServConfiguration.name: dhcpServConfiguration
dhcpServConfiguration.description: Objects that contain pre-configured and Dynamic Config. Info.

dhcpServFailover.name: dhcpServFailover
dhcpServFailover.description: Objects that contain partner server info.

DhcpServTimeInterval.name: DhcpServTimeInterval
DhcpServTimeInterval.description: The number of milli-seconds that has elapsed since some epoch. Systems that cannot measure events to the milli-second resolution SHOULD round this value to the next available resolution that the system supports.

dhcpServSystemDescr.name: dhcpServSystemDescr
dhcpServSystemDescr.description: A textual description of the server. This value should include the full name and version identification of the server. This string MUST contain only printable NVT ASCII characters.

dhcpServSystemUpTime.name: dhcpServSystemUpTime
dhcpServSystemUpTime.description: If the server has a persistent state (e.g., a process), this value will be the seconds elapsed since it started. For software without persistant state, this value will be zero.

dhcpServSystemResetTime.name: dhcpServSystemResetTime
dhcpServSystemResetTime.description: If the server has a persistent state (e.g., a process) and supports a `reset' operation (e.g., can be told to re-read configuration files), this value will be the seconds elapsed since the last time the name server was `reset.' For software that does not have persistence or does not support a `reset' operation, this value will be zero.

dhcpServCountUsedSubnets.name: dhcpServCountUsedSubnets
dhcpServCountUsedSubnets.description: The number subnets managed by the server (i.e. configured), from which the server has issued at least one lease.

dhcpServCountUnusedSubnets.name: dhcpServCountUnusedSubnets
dhcpServCountUnusedSubnets.description: The number subnets managed by the server (i.e. configured), from which the server has issued no leases.

dhcpServCountFullSubnets.name: dhcpServCountFullSubnets
dhcpServCountFullSubnets.description: The number subnets managed by the server (i.e. configured), in which the address pools have been exhausted.

dhcpServBootpCountRequests.name: dhcpServBootpCountRequests
dhcpServBootpCountRequests.description: The number of packets received that contain a Message Type of 1 (BOOTREQUEST) in the first octet and do not contain option number 53 (DHCP Message Type) in the options.

dhcpServBootpCountInvalids.name: dhcpServBootpCountInvalids
dhcpServBootpCountInvalids.description: The number of packets received that do not contain a Message Type of 1 (BOOTREQUEST) in the first octet or are not valid BOOTP packets (e.g.: too short, invalid field in packet header).

dhcpServBootpCountReplies.name: dhcpServBootpCountReplies
dhcpServBootpCountReplies.description: The number of packets sent that contain a Message Type of 1 (BOOTREQUEST) in the first octet and do not contain option number 53 (DHCP Message Type) in the options.

dhcpServBootpCountDroppedUnknownClients.name: dhcpServBootpCountDroppedUnknownClients
dhcpServBootpCountDroppedUnknownClients.description: The number of BOOTP packets dropped due to the server not recognizing or not providing service to the hardware address received in the incoming packet.

dhcpServBootpCountDroppedNotServingSubne.name: dhcpServBootpCountDroppedNotServingSubnet
dhcpServBootpCountDroppedNotServingSubne.description: The number of BOOTP packets dropped due to the server not being configured or not otherwise able to serve addresses on the subnet from which this message was received.

dhcpServDhcpCountDiscovers.name: dhcpServDhcpCountDiscovers
dhcpServDhcpCountDiscovers.description: The number of DHCPDISCOVER (option 53 with value 1) packets received.

dhcpServDhcpCountRequests.name: dhcpServDhcpCountRequests
dhcpServDhcpCountRequests.description: The number of DHCPREQUEST (option 53 with value 3) packets received.

dhcpServDhcpCountReleases.name: dhcpServDhcpCountReleases
dhcpServDhcpCountReleases.description: The number of DHCPRELEASE (option 53 with value 7) packets received.

dhcpServDhcpCountDeclines.name: dhcpServDhcpCountDeclines
dhcpServDhcpCountDeclines.description: The number of DHCPDECLINE (option 53 with value 4) packets received.

dhcpServDhcpCountInforms.name: dhcpServDhcpCountInforms
dhcpServDhcpCountInforms.description: The number of DHCPINFORM (option 53 with value 8) packets received.

dhcpServDhcpCountInvalids.name: dhcpServDhcpCountInvalids
dhcpServDhcpCountInvalids.description: The number of DHCP packets received whose DHCP message type (i.e.: option number 53) is not understood or handled by the server.

dhcpServDhcpCountOffers.name: dhcpServDhcpCountOffers
dhcpServDhcpCountOffers.description: The number of DHCPOFFER (option 53 with value 2) packets sent.

dhcpServDhcpCountAcks.name: dhcpServDhcpCountAcks
dhcpServDhcpCountAcks.description: The number of DHCPACK (option 53 with value 5) packets sent.

dhcpServDhcpCountNacks.name: dhcpServDhcpCountNacks
dhcpServDhcpCountNacks.description: The number of DHCPNACK (option 53 with value 6) packets sent.

dhcpServDhcpCountDroppedUnknownClient.name: dhcpServDhcpCountDroppedUnknownClient
dhcpServDhcpCountDroppedUnknownClient.description: The number of DHCP packets dropped due to the server not recognizing or not providing service to the client-id and/or hardware address received in the incoming packet.

dhcpServDhcpCountDroppedNotServingSubnet.name: dhcpServDhcpCountDroppedNotServingSubnet
dhcpServDhcpCountDroppedNotServingSubnet.description: The number of DHCP packets dropped due to the server not being configured or not otherwise able to serve addresses on the subnet from which this message was received.

dhcpServBootpStatMinArrivalInterval.name: dhcpServBootpStatMinArrivalInterval
dhcpServBootpStatMinArrivalInterval.description: The minimum amount of time between receiving two BOOTP messages. A message is received at the server when the server is able to begin processing the message. This typically occurs immediately after the message is read into server memory. If no messages have been received, then this object contains a zero value.

dhcpServBootpStatMaxArrivalInterval.name: dhcpServBootpStatMaxArrivalInterval
dhcpServBootpStatMaxArrivalInterval.description: The maximum amount of time between receiving two BOOTP messages. A message is received at the server when the server is able to begin processing the message. This typically occurs immediately after the message is read into server memory. If no messages have been received, then this object contains a zero value.

dhcpServBootpStatLastArrivalTime.name: dhcpServBootpStatLastArrivalTime
dhcpServBootpStatLastArrivalTime.description: The number of seconds since the last valid BOOTP message was received by the server. Invalid messages do not cause this value to change. If valid no messages have been received, then this object contains a zero value.

dhcpServBootpStatMinResponseTime.name: dhcpServBootpStatMinResponseTime
dhcpServBootpStatMinResponseTime.description: The smallest time interval measured as the difference between the arrival of a BOOTP message at the server and the successful transmission of the response to that message. A message is received at the server when the server is able to begin processing the message. A message is transmitted after the server has no further use for the message. Note that the operating system may still have the message queued internally. The operating system queue time is not to be considered as part of the response time. Invalid messages do not cause this value to change. If no valid messages have been received, then this object contains a zero value.

dhcpServBootpStatMaxResponseTime.name: dhcpServBootpStatMaxResponseTime
dhcpServBootpStatMaxResponseTime.description: The largest time interval measured as the difference between the arrival of a BOOTP message at the server and the successful transmission of the response to that message. A message is received at the server when the server is able to begin processing the message. A message is transmitted after the server has no further use for the message. Note that the operating system may still have the message queued internally. The operating system queue time is not to be considered as part of the response time. Invalid messages do not cause this value to change. If no valid messages have been received, then this object contains a zero value.

dhcpServBootpStatSumResponseTime.name: dhcpServBootpStatSumResponseTime
dhcpServBootpStatSumResponseTime.description: The sum of the response time intervals in milli-seconds where a response time interval is measured as the difference between the arrival of a BOOTP message at the server and the successful transmission of the response to that message. A message is received at the server when the server is able to begin processing the message. A message is transmitted after the server has no further use for the message. Note that the operating system may still have the message queued internally. The operating system queue time is not to be considered as part of the response time. Invalid messages do not cause this value to change. If no valid messages have been received, then this object contains a zero value.

dhcpServDhcpStatMinArrivalInterval.name: dhcpServDhcpStatMinArrivalInterval
dhcpServDhcpStatMinArrivalInterval.description: The minimum amount of time between receiving two DHCP messages. A message is received at the server when the server is able to begin processing the message. This typically occurs immediately after the message is read into server memory. If no messages have been received, then this object contains a zero value.

dhcpServDhcpStatMaxArrivalInterval.name: dhcpServDhcpStatMaxArrivalInterval
dhcpServDhcpStatMaxArrivalInterval.description: The maximum amount of time between receiving two DHCP messages. A message is received at the server when the server is able to begin processing the message. This typically occurs immediately after the message is read into server memory. If no messages have been received, then this object contains a zero value.

dhcpServDhcpStatLastArrivalTime.name: dhcpServDhcpStatLastArrivalTime
dhcpServDhcpStatLastArrivalTime.description: The number of seconds since the last valid DHCP message was received by the server. Invalid messages do not cause this value to change. If no valid messages have been received, then this object contains a zero value.

dhcpServRangeTable.name: dhcpServRangeTable
dhcpServRangeTable.description: A list of ranges that are configured on this server.

dhcpServRangeEntry.name: dhcpServRangeEntry
dhcpServRangeEntry.description: A logical row in the serverRangeTable.

dhcpServRangeSubnetAddr.name: dhcpServRangeSubnetAddr
dhcpServRangeSubnetAddr.description: The IP address defining a subnet

dhcpServRangeSubnetMask.name: dhcpServRangeSubnetMask
dhcpServRangeSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask (DHCP option 1) provided to any client offered an address from this range.

dhcpServRangeStart.name: dhcpServRangeStart
dhcpServRangeStart.description: Start of Subnet Address, Index for Conceptual Tabl, Type IP address

dhcpServRangeEnd.name: dhcpServRangeEnd
dhcpServRangeEnd.description: The IP address of the last address in the range. The value of range end must be greater than or equal to the value of range start.

dhcpServRangeInUse.name: dhcpServRangeInUse
dhcpServRangeInUse.description: The number of addresses in this range that are currently in use. This number includes those addresses whose lease has not expired and addresses which have been reserved (either by the server or through configuration).

dhcpServRangeOutstandingOffers.name: dhcpServRangeOutstandingOffers
dhcpServRangeOutstandingOffers.description: The number of outstanding DHCPOFFER messages for this range is reported with this value. An offer is outstanding if the server has sent a DHCPOFFER message to a client, but has not yet received a DHCPREQUEST message from the client nor has the server-specific timeout (limiting the time in which a client can respond to the offer message) for the offer message expired.

dhcpServRangeUnavailable.name: dhcpServRangeUnavailable
dhcpServRangeUnavailable.description: Dhcp Server IP Addresses unavailable in a Subnet

dhcpServRangeUnused.name: dhcpServRangeUnused
dhcpServRangeUnused.description: The number of addresses in this range that are currently unused. This number includes those addresses whose lease has not expired and addresses which have been reserved (either by the server or through configuration).

dhcpServFailoverEntry.name: dhcpServFailoverEntry
dhcpServFailoverEntry.description: A logical row in the serverFailoverTable.

dhcpServFailoverPartnerAddr.name: dhcpServFailoverPartnerAddr
dhcpServFailoverPartnerAddr.description: The IP address defining a partner server

dhcpServFailoverPartnerPolltime.name: dhcpServFailoverPartnerPolltime
dhcpServFailoverPartnerPolltime.description: The last time there was a successfull communication with the partner server. This value is local time in seconds since some epoch.

ipspgDhcpTrapTable.name: ipspgDhcpTrapTable
ipspgDhcpTrapTable.description: The agent's table of IPSPG alarm information.

ipspgDhcpTrapEntry.name: ipspgDhcpTrapEntry
ipspgDhcpTrapEntry.description: Information about the last alarm trap generated by the agent.

ipspgDhcpTrIndex.name: ipspgDhcpTrIndex
ipspgDhcpTrIndex.description: Index into the IPSPG Alarm traps

ipspgDhcpTrSequence.name: ipspgDhcpTrSequence
ipspgDhcpTrSequence.description: Counter of the number of IPSPG alarm traps since the agent was last initialized

ipspgDhcpTrId.name: ipspgDhcpTrId
ipspgDhcpTrId.description: The application which generated this IPSPG alarm.

ipspgDhcpTrText.name: ipspgDhcpTrText
ipspgDhcpTrText.description: An ASCII string describing the IPSPG alarm condition/cause.

ipspgDhcpTrPriority.name: ipspgDhcpTrPriority
ipspgDhcpTrPriority.description: The priority level as set on the agent for this Calss and Type of trap.

ipspgDhcpTrClass.name: ipspgDhcpTrClass
ipspgDhcpTrClass.description: The Class number of the described IPSPG alarm.

ipspgDhcpTrType.name: ipspgDhcpTrType
ipspgDhcpTrType.description: The type number of the described IPSPG alarm.

ipspgDhcpTrTime.name: ipspgDhcpTrTime
ipspgDhcpTrTime.description: The time that the condition or event occurred which caused generation of this alarm. This value is given in seconds since 00:00:00 Greenwich mean time (GMT) January 1, 1970.

ipspgDhcpTrSuspect.name: ipspgDhcpTrSuspect
ipspgDhcpTrSuspect.description: An ASCII string describing the host which caused the IPSPG alarm.

ipspgDhcpTrDiagId.name: ipspgDhcpTrDiagId
ipspgDhcpTrDiagId.description: An integer describing the diagnosis which triggered this IPSPG alarm.

dhcpServerStarted.name: dhcpServerStarted
dhcpServerStarted.description: The monitor has determined that the DHCP server has been started.

dhcpServerStopped.name: dhcpServerStopped
dhcpServerStopped.description: The monitor has determined that the DHCP server has been stopped.

dhcpServerReload.name: dhcpServerReload
dhcpServerReload.description: The monitor has determined that the DHCP server has been reloaded.

dhcpServerSubnetDepleted.name: dhcpServerSubnetDepleted
dhcpServerSubnetDepleted.description: The monitor has determined that the DHCP server has run out of addresses in a subnet.

dhcpServerBadPacket.name: dhcpServerBadPacket
dhcpServerBadPacket.description: The monitor has determined that the DHCP server has received a bad DHCP or Bootp packet.

dhcpServerFailoverActive.name: dhcpServerFailoverActive
dhcpServerFailoverActive.description: This trap is issued by the secondary server. It indicates a primary partner server is down and its scopes are now being served by this failover server.

dhcpServerFailoverReturnedControl.name: dhcpServerFailoverReturnedControl
dhcpServerFailoverReturnedControl.description: This trap is issued by the secondary server. It indicates that the failover server has returned control to its primary partner.

dhcpServerSubnetThresholdExceeded.name: dhcpServerSubnetThresholdExceeded
dhcpServerSubnetThresholdExceeded.description: This trap is issued when subnet threshold is exceeded.

dhcpServerSubnetThresholdDescent.name: dhcpServerSubnetThresholdDescent
dhcpServerSubnetThresholdDescent.description: This trap is issued when subnet unavailable lease percentage falls below the descent threshold value.

dhcpServerDropUnknownClient.name: dhcpServerDropUnknownClient
dhcpServerDropUnknownClient.description: This trap is issued when the server drops a client message because the client MAC address is either in a MAC exclusion pool or is not in an inclusion pool.

dhcpServerPingResponseReceived.name: dhcpServerPingResponseReceived
dhcpServerPingResponseReceived.description: This trap is issued when the server receives a ping response.
